1
00:00:48,710 --> 00:00:52,270
[Jirisan]

2
00:00:52,270 --> 00:00:57,140
[The places, people, organizations, accidents, and the background stories depicted in this drama are fictional]

3
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:00,944
Someone died because of a potato bomb.

4
00:01:00,944 --> 00:01:02,420
But did someone die because of it?

5
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:05,598
Someone left it there on purpose to kill people.

6
00:01:05,598 --> 00:01:08,115
- Who did that?
- Yi Kang.

7
00:01:08,115 --> 00:01:10,512
He's Yang Sun's cousin?

8
00:01:10,512 --> 00:01:12,664
- Where's Yang Sun?
- Yang Sun!

9
00:01:12,664 --> 00:01:14,465
Yang Sun.

10
00:01:16,050 --> 00:01:17,894
Se Wook... told me.

11
00:01:17,894 --> 00:01:21,314
He might have put it there to kill the grandpa.

12
00:01:21,314 --> 00:01:24,484
Or maybe he was aiming for someone else.

13
00:01:24,484 --> 00:01:26,319
Are you sure you saw my grandpa?

14
00:01:26,319 --> 00:01:28,897
He led Yang Sun there on purpose.

15
00:01:28,897 --> 00:01:30,460
No.

16
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:33,090
Someone noticed our plan.

17
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:36,940
It was one of the rangers.

18
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:39,332
Lee Se Wook!

19
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:41,000
No, he's not home.

20
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,518
I lied. To kill you.

21
00:01:43,518 --> 00:01:45,913
Yang Sun!

22
00:01:51,177 --> 00:01:54,389
But... that wasn't the end.

23
00:01:54,389 --> 00:01:57,492
There was someone else. The real criminal.

24
00:01:57,492 --> 00:01:59,827
Can you help me?

25
00:02:03,148 --> 00:02:05,666
What can I do?

26
00:02:11,831 --> 00:02:14,817
You can see Mount Jirisan at a glance.

27
00:02:14,817 --> 00:02:16,318
Wait.

28
00:02:17,028 --> 00:02:19,748
Is that Cheonwangbong Peak?

29
00:02:19,748 --> 00:02:23,931
No way. You can't see all of it at a glance.

30
00:02:23,931 --> 00:02:27,272
Mount Jirisan includes way over Cheonwangbong Peak.

31
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:30,975
Jirisan is indeed far and wide.

32
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:37,887
By the way, where could Lee Se Wook have gone?

33
00:02:37,887 --> 00:02:41,536
We've searched for two months, but he's nowhere to be seen.

34
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:44,705
There's no trace of him coming down, either.

35
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:53,422
- What about that thing?
- Sorry?

36
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:58,909
You don't see anything these days? You haven't mentioned it in months.

37
00:02:58,909 --> 00:03:01,839
I haven't seen anything after that.

38
00:03:02,373 --> 00:03:04,250
That's good.

39
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:08,345
Yes, I guess so.

40
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:15,895
Our day off starts in just a couple of hours.

41
00:03:15,895 --> 00:03:18,989
Any plans? It's the Christmas holiday.

42
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:22,510
Stupid Christmas. I hate it.

43
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:25,521
Let's go. Back to patrol.

44
00:03:31,319 --> 00:03:36,555
[You didn't forget our Christmas date, right? Don't be late this time.]

45
00:03:43,089 --> 00:03:47,185
Over here. On three!

46
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:49,629
One, two, three!

47
00:03:49,629 --> 00:03:51,205
That's nice.

48
00:03:51,205 --> 00:03:54,074
Over here, Sir! One, two, three!

49
00:03:55,744 --> 00:03:57,762
One, two, three!

50
00:03:57,762 --> 00:04:02,313
- It's snowing! It really feels like Christmas.
- Come help if you have time to take pictures.

51
00:04:02,313 --> 00:04:05,653
Should we take one in front of the tree?

52
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:10,832
We're fine. You two go ahead.

53
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,080
See you later.

54
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,170
Party poopers.

55
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:18,270
Let's just take a selfie, the two of us.

56
00:04:19,909 --> 00:04:23,011
Smile!

57
00:04:28,242 --> 00:04:30,586
That looks nice.

58
00:04:33,131 --> 00:04:35,741
What are you doing this Christmas?

59
00:04:37,418 --> 00:04:38,945
Nothing much.

60
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:42,656
If you don't have plans, do you want to go here with me?

61
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:46,159
It's called Penguin Swimming Festival. You get to swim in the winter sea.

62
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:50,056
First place wins a 5-day trip to Southeast Asia.

63
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:52,274
Is he serious?

64
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:57,505
Thanks, but...

65
00:04:57,505 --> 00:05:02,949
There's still time to think. Take a look and let me know.

66
00:05:02,949 --> 00:05:06,622
The prizes are great this year.

67
00:05:11,644 --> 00:05:13,922
Hey, I'm in trouble.

68
00:05:13,922 --> 00:05:18,640
That jerk, Il Hae... He's asking me to take his shelter shift for him.

69
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:22,013
Otherwise, I have to pay him back what I owe right now.

70
00:05:22,013 --> 00:05:25,183
Can you please take the shift?

71
00:05:25,183 --> 00:05:26,684
I have plans today.

72
00:05:26,684 --> 00:05:32,661
But today is the day for me! I'm finally watching a movie with Yang Sun.

73
00:05:32,661 --> 00:05:37,609
I've been waiting for this day for years. Please?

74
00:05:37,609 --> 00:05:39,322
Why don't you ask Yi Kang?

75
00:05:39,322 --> 00:05:43,300
She's already been called in. Remember?

76
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:45,761
Ten scallion pancakes and a wish.

77
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:50,958
And Yi Kang needs you by her side.

78
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:55,237
- Thanks!
- What?

79
00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:04,694
You guys are amazing. Seo Yi Kang. Kang Hyun Jo.

80
00:06:04,694 --> 00:06:08,442
You guys are the needle and the thread of Jirisan. So fast!

81
00:06:08,442 --> 00:06:09,811
I appreciate it, too.

82
00:06:09,811 --> 00:06:12,814
Today's the anniversary of my father's death.

83
00:06:12,814 --> 00:06:14,582
I'll get going then.

84
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:17,924
Oh, right. Merry Christmas.

85
00:06:17,924 --> 00:06:19,845
Merry Christmas.

86
00:06:20,938 --> 00:06:25,515
You're just as lame as I am. Do you really want to work on Christmas?

87
00:06:25,515 --> 00:06:27,970
Don't you have plans?

88
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,860
Let's just say I don't.

89
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,840
[Bidam Shelter]

90
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:34,544
But who's the needle and who's the thread?

91
00:06:34,544 --> 00:06:36,854
Does that even matter?

92
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:42,106
This is the shelter. Maximum capacity 20. That door leads to the office.

93
00:06:43,052 --> 00:06:44,595
This is the office.

94
00:06:44,595 --> 00:06:47,265
The shop closes at nine. The equipment is in there.

95
00:06:47,265 --> 00:06:51,034
And this is the lost and found.

96
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:56,938
That's the storage with a generator. It gets fussy in the winter.

97
00:06:56,938 --> 00:07:01,112
If that happens, you can refer to the manual in the desk drawer to fix it.

98
00:07:01,112 --> 00:07:02,370
Shall we get started?

99
00:07:02,370 --> 00:07:05,270
Sorry? Start what?

100
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:10,330
Oh, gosh!

101
00:07:10,330 --> 00:07:13,073
- Are you okay?
- Goodness.

102
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:27,830
Really? That's not going to get any dust out.

103
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,431
Step aside.

104
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:33,383
Like this. Beat it like this.

105
00:07:33,383 --> 00:07:36,928
Like this! Do it like this!

106
00:07:36,928 --> 00:07:38,331
Like this?

107
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:43,591
That's not it! Like this! Try it!

108
00:07:44,246 --> 00:07:46,755
- Jeez.
- What?

109
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:54,153
Look at you. Can't you fold them neatly?

110
00:07:54,153 --> 00:07:58,566
I am! In case you forgot, I used to be a soldier.

111
00:07:58,566 --> 00:08:02,498
Once you're done, go organize the equipment in the cabinet.

112
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:09,501
- Demon Seo...
- I can hear you. Get going!

113
00:08:09,501 --> 00:08:11,390
Yes, Ma'am.

114
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:16,090
[Watch Your Step]

115
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,486
Bidam Shelter.

116
00:08:23,486 --> 00:08:26,531
It's me, Il Hae. I forgot to tell you earlier.

117
00:08:26,531 --> 00:08:28,825
Someone's supposed to come and pick up a lost article today.

118
00:08:28,825 --> 00:08:31,259
There's a note in the log that you can check.

119
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:33,720
Okay. I got it.

120
00:08:35,106 --> 00:08:37,299
The lost and found log...

121
00:08:37,299 --> 00:08:39,502
Why? What is it?

122
00:08:39,502 --> 00:08:44,396
Someone is coming to pick up a lost article. But where's the log?

123
00:08:44,396 --> 00:08:46,575
Oh, that.

124
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,294
Here.

125
00:08:53,330 --> 00:08:55,092
[Lost and Found General Record]

126
00:08:55,092 --> 00:08:58,610
Wait. This must be him. Right?

127
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:00,750
The blue rucksack. Yim Cheol Gyeong.

128
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:03,890
[Yim Cheol Gyeong]

129
00:09:12,985 --> 00:09:16,072
Why? Is there a problem?

130
00:09:16,072 --> 00:09:17,556
What?

131
00:09:18,991 --> 00:09:20,684
No.

132
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,521
Gosh, it's snowing.

133
00:09:49,071 --> 00:09:51,540
Did you check the weather?

134
00:09:52,483 --> 00:09:55,852
There was a snowstorm warning for tonight.

135
00:09:57,405 --> 00:09:59,949
It's a real white Christmas.

136
00:10:01,584 --> 00:10:04,019
Up here on the mountain is a different world.

137
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:07,772
It may be nice down there, but snow is your worst enemy here.

138
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:11,109
Your vision gets blurry in snow, and the chance of getting lost goes up.

139
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:15,597
If your socks get wet by accident, having hypothermia is a matter of time.

140
00:10:15,597 --> 00:10:17,658
In a nutshell...

141
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:21,762
it's killer weather.

142
00:10:21,762 --> 00:10:28,325
But people down there must be happy. Don't you think?

143
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:04,212
Help your neighbors.

144
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:07,799
Thank you.

145
00:11:29,313 --> 00:11:34,867
I'll see you at 2:00 p.m. outside the movie theater.

146
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:38,700
[No Vehicles Allowed]

147
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:43,190
[Jungsalli Hiking Information Center]

148
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:47,500
Your call cannot be completed...

149
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,956
The Jeonnam Regional Police Agency

150
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:55,834
has arrested Police Officer Lieutenant Yim

151
00:13:55,835 --> 00:14:00,889
for receiving money and valuables multiple times from a drug dealer.

152
00:14:00,889 --> 00:14:05,510
Lieutenant Yim has allegedly received a total of some hundred million won.

153
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:10,541
And in return has given away confidential information on drug crime investigation.

154
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:12,559
The police have issued a search warrant...

155
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:15,353
- Yim Cheol Gyeong?
- Yes!

156
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:18,314
Isn't that a funny name?

157
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:22,610
Yi Kang was all over that punk.

158
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:26,273
There she goes again. We can tell you're drunk.

159
00:14:26,273 --> 00:14:28,908
Yi Kang was like 14, I believe

160
00:14:28,909 --> 00:14:31,077
when she ran away to the mountain

161
00:14:31,078 --> 00:14:34,539
and came back after 3 days,

162
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:38,034
but with a broken arm this time.

163
00:14:38,034 --> 00:14:40,253
I couldn't just let her be.

164
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:45,091
So I sent her to the training center for problematic children in Jirisan.

165
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:49,354
But that's where something happened!

166
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:56,161
Welcome to Cheongwon Training Center.

167
00:14:56,161 --> 00:15:00,799
During the three days of your stay, you must comply with our rules.

168
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:06,262
First, bring your cell phones and personal items to the front.

169
00:15:06,262 --> 00:15:07,864
He's so impudent.

170
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,616
- He scares me.
- What are you doing?

171
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:11,409
- What are you doing?
- Give that back!

172
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:14,019
- I need to submit this too?
- Let's go home!

173
00:15:14,019 --> 00:15:17,073
- What are you doing?
- Mom.

174
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:23,730
How scary. He doesn't scare me.

175
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:25,065
I've made a bad decision.

176
00:15:25,065 --> 00:15:28,001
When will this end? Can I leave now?

177
00:15:28,001 --> 00:15:30,411
I miss my mom.

178
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:33,681
You'll be doing boot training from here to Cheonwangbong Peak.

179
00:15:33,682 --> 00:15:35,543
First place gets 50K won gift certificate.

180
00:15:35,543 --> 00:15:38,144
Second place 30K won, third place 20K won.

181
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:40,897
And the last one will clean the toilet.

182
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:44,218
How about the winner-takes-all?

183
00:15:44,218 --> 00:15:46,546
- Yes!
- Yes!

184
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:49,247
Hurry!

185
00:15:56,789 --> 00:15:58,457
[Cheongwon Training Center]

186
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,027
I can't do this!

187
00:16:42,651 --> 00:16:44,277
Take my hand.

188
00:16:44,277 --> 00:16:45,962
No, thanks.

189
00:17:14,093 --> 00:17:16,461
That was something.

190
00:17:39,483 --> 00:17:43,868
- There comes the last one.
- Why are they so late, though?

191
00:17:43,868 --> 00:17:46,881
- Wasn't he in front of us?
- Be careful.

192
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:53,204
- The other one got hurt or something?
- Yes, it seems he got hurt.

193
00:17:53,204 --> 00:17:56,540
I'm just so worn out.

194
00:18:02,356 --> 00:18:04,332
Great job, everyone.

195
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:08,069
Now you've made it to the top.

196
00:18:08,069 --> 00:18:11,180
Why don't we scream out loud?

197
00:18:15,353 --> 00:18:21,766
All right. Everyone, scream and get some burdens off of your minds.

198
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:33,736
Hey, shout out something.

199
00:18:33,737 --> 00:18:37,298
Maybe something to your parents.

200
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:42,578
I have no parents.

201
00:19:14,136 --> 00:19:16,663
Hey, Yi Kang!

202
00:19:19,534 --> 00:19:22,088
Where are you going?

203
00:19:22,088 --> 00:19:25,173
Well... I'm waiting for the bus.

204
00:19:25,173 --> 00:19:27,415
What? What are you saying?

205
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,401
Our house is right here!

206
00:19:29,401 --> 00:19:32,777
Where are you going to run off to again? Come with me!

207
00:19:35,324 --> 00:19:37,033
Right now!

208
00:19:56,461 --> 00:19:59,954
What was that? That brat!

209
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:21,344
There's nothing much inside.

210
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:26,558
But it must be something special if he's coming on Christmas day.

211
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:28,885
Maybe it's a present from someone.

212
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:35,676
You've been awfully quiet.

213
00:20:35,676 --> 00:20:37,585
What's wrong?

214
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:39,788
What?

215
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:41,739
No.

216
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,892
I'm totally fine.

217
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:47,995
Bidam Shelter.

218
00:20:47,996 --> 00:20:50,873
Main Station speaking. We have an SOS.

219
00:20:50,874 --> 00:20:53,459
Sprained ankle on the way to Bidam Shelter.

220
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:57,380
- Location?
- Next to the old tree by Sonbawi Rock.

221
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:04,009
Is that the one who said he's coming to the shelter today?

222
00:21:04,721 --> 00:21:06,305
I haven't checked that.

223
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,474
The signal must've been weak because of the weather.

224
00:21:08,475 --> 00:21:10,018
The call got cut off.

225
00:21:11,436 --> 00:21:14,681
We'll get going soon. It will take about an hour.

226
00:21:21,054 --> 00:21:23,406
- I'll come, too.
- You stay here.

227
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,449
You're going up alone in this weather?

228
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:27,644
One of us has to man the shelter.

229
00:21:27,644 --> 00:21:29,654
Then I'll go.

230
00:21:31,665 --> 00:21:33,457
I know the mountain better than you.

231
00:21:33,458 --> 00:21:36,003
If anything happens, I can contact Jangteomok for backup.

232
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:37,696
So stay here.

233
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:43,410
Senior.

234
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:49,625
Radio me if anything happens. I'll come right away.

235
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:52,560
How reliable. You're all grown up now.

236
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,228
I've been, for a while.

237
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:56,815
Just don't fall asleep and miss the radio.

238
00:22:17,335 --> 00:22:19,838
Illegal hiking on such a day?

239
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:22,157
Check the license plate.

240
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:31,432
Sir! This vehicle is on the wanted list.

241
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:34,093
- What?
- A wanted car!

242
00:22:46,448 --> 00:22:48,108
Bidam Shelter.

243
00:22:48,108 --> 00:22:51,887
I heard a weird noise from the 11:00 o'clock direction.

244
00:22:51,887 --> 00:22:54,289
Yi Kang, are you all right?

245
00:22:54,289 --> 00:22:56,600
I heard nothing.

246
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,877
Main Station, night duty room. It might be a snow avalanche. We'll check.

247
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:03,614
100m to Sonbawi Rock. I'll radio again when I get there.

248
00:23:26,113 --> 00:23:27,947
My goodness!

249
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:33,619
- What are you doing?
- Open the door.

250
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:35,647
Seriously...

251
00:23:35,647 --> 00:23:37,273
Gosh...

252
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:45,282
Hurry.

253
00:23:45,282 --> 00:23:47,942
Hurry up and give it to me.

254
00:23:48,718 --> 00:23:49,927
I'm coming.

255
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:51,954
Hurry, hurry.

256
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:56,159
Gosh, it's hot.

257
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:00,855
Come on.

258
00:24:00,856 --> 00:24:03,858
You should be keeping people from hiking in this weather.

259
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:05,526
What were you thinking?

260
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:08,070
Gosh, it's so warm and nice.

261
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:11,283
Hey, I brought chicken for you guys.

262
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:13,200
That's not chicken.

263
00:24:13,201 --> 00:24:14,743
That's a box of ice.

264
00:24:14,744 --> 00:24:18,322
Stop being mean. I didn't have anywhere to go.

265
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:22,877
I...

266
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:26,005
got stood up.

267
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:08,848
I wanted to meet someone and feel better.

268
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:12,977
Since it's Christmas.

269
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:17,615
But there was no place for me but the mountain.

270
00:25:19,601 --> 00:25:20,768
My nose is runny.

271
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:24,105
I've surely caught a cold.

272
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,265
It's freezing here.

273
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:29,785
You'd better clean these.

274
00:25:38,050 --> 00:25:40,870
[Yim Cheol Gyeong]

275
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:42,715
Wait, this is...

276
00:25:44,184 --> 00:25:45,526
What?

277
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:50,523
- What's wrong?
- It's Yi Kang's first love.

278
00:25:50,523 --> 00:25:52,716
That's him. Yim Cheol Gyeong.

279
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:54,927
It's a unique name, so I remember.

280
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:58,623
Right, he's the same age as her. This is him.

281
00:25:58,623 --> 00:26:03,077
You know how Yi Kang blabbers on about her past when she's drunk.

282
00:26:03,928 --> 00:26:06,923
Yim Cheol Gyeong. Yi Kang's first love.

283
00:26:06,923 --> 00:26:08,508
Where did she say they met for the first time?

284
00:26:08,508 --> 00:26:12,095
I think it was at some delinquent teen group in Jirisan.

285
00:26:12,095 --> 00:26:16,031
When Yi Kang ran away from home and went to Seoul, she bumped into him again.

286
00:26:16,032 --> 00:26:17,242
Like destiny.
[22 March 2002]

287
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:21,380
