288
00:26:21,380 --> 00:26:23,550
[Segang Daily]

289
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:26,720
♫ Wake up! ♫

290
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:38,530
[Grand Opening]

291
00:26:45,645 --> 00:26:48,439
We'll do great at World Cup! And so will you!

292
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:51,801
Let's go, everyone!

293
00:26:51,801 --> 00:26:53,444
Let's go!

294
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:56,488
Here, take one! Let's go, everyone!

295
00:26:56,489 --> 00:26:58,657
We've got this!

296
00:26:58,658 --> 00:27:00,735
Thank you.

297
00:27:06,916 --> 00:27:08,043
Take one!

298
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:12,260
♫ Do your best and don't ignore me ♫

299
00:27:12,260 --> 00:27:16,300
♫ Shut your eyes to our abandoned memories ♫

300
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:18,380
Take one!

301
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:22,390
♫ Tell me again one more time ♫

302
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:24,430
You're Jirisan, right?

303
00:27:27,937 --> 00:27:29,805
Or are you a soccer ball?

304
00:27:35,236 --> 00:27:37,029
Did you run away again?

305
00:27:38,022 --> 00:27:39,340
What?

306
00:27:40,525 --> 00:27:42,093
Here.

307
00:27:42,093 --> 00:27:44,929
The food's not great, but cheap.

308
00:27:44,929 --> 00:27:47,339
Come by some time with your grandma.

309
00:27:53,421 --> 00:27:55,121
Hey!

310
00:28:03,848 --> 00:28:06,101
How much?

311
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:07,501
What?

312
00:28:08,645 --> 00:28:11,389
The restaurant. How much do they pay you?

313
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:15,859
- Go, Korea!
- Go, Korea!

314
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:17,903
- Go, Korea!
- Go, Korea!

315
00:28:17,904 --> 00:28:20,781
Get back home right away! Are you giving up on a college?

316
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:22,658
I am studying!

317
00:28:22,659 --> 00:28:24,535
- You need to retake the entrance exam!
- Oh, come on!

318
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:27,079
I know you're not studying!

319
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:30,408
Grandma, I'm busy. I'll call you back.

320
00:28:34,754 --> 00:28:36,713
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

321
00:28:36,714 --> 00:28:38,424
One more soju, please.

322
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:40,008
- One more soju?
- Can you get us this too?

323
00:28:40,009 --> 00:28:41,553
- Thank you.
- No problem.

324
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,440
[I can do it!]

325
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,180
[Make sure to read the questions carefully and slowly!!]

326
00:29:06,180 --> 00:29:07,880
[I can beat myself and my fate, too!]

327
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:09,330
[Conquer the CSATs!]

328
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:11,330
[Wake up! There's no time for this!]

329
00:29:18,481 --> 00:29:20,732
Oh, gosh.

330
00:29:23,740 --> 00:29:26,630
[Class of 2003 College Scholastic Ability Test]

331
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:29,559
- You've got this!
- You've got this!

332
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:32,394
- Good luck!
- You can do it!

333
00:29:32,395 --> 00:29:34,805
- Good luck!
- Good luck!

334
00:29:36,566 --> 00:29:39,027
Yes! You've got this.

335
00:29:40,111 --> 00:29:42,530
Good luck!

336
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:45,642
You can do it!

337
00:29:45,642 --> 00:29:49,269
- Good luck!
- You'll do great!

338
00:30:10,583 --> 00:30:12,793
Have you seen the beach?

339
00:30:15,021 --> 00:30:16,456
Yes.

340
00:30:16,456 --> 00:30:18,607
On TV.

341
00:30:33,860 --> 00:30:37,940
♫ Shine along ♫

342
00:30:37,940 --> 00:30:42,220
♫ The leaves they dance and speak ♫

343
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:46,740
♫ And sway... And your ♫

344
00:30:46,740 --> 00:30:50,840
♫ colors they remind me ♫

345
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:56,390
♫ When the wind sings ♫

346
00:30:56,390 --> 00:31:00,690
♫ I'll know that you're sound and safe ♫

347
00:31:00,700 --> 00:31:03,990
♫ I can feel you ♫

348
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:11,120
♫ Still loneliness in your gaze ♫

349
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:15,710
♫ I wish you'd stay... ♫

350
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:19,585
How bad was it?

351
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:23,972
I think I got one or two right.

352
00:31:25,370 --> 00:31:29,620
♫ It's all I ever wanted ♫

353
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:32,990
♫ I wish you'd stay ♫

354
00:31:32,990 --> 00:31:35,759
Can I ask you something?

355
00:31:36,394 --> 00:31:38,863
Why did you hit me

356
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,890
at the bus stop?

357
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:46,860
♫ I wish you'd stay without me ♫

358
00:31:48,730 --> 00:31:52,790
♫ Shine under ♫

359
00:31:52,790 --> 00:31:57,240
♫ the drive so we can move ♫

360
00:31:57,240 --> 00:32:01,730
♫ And all you meant ♫

361
00:32:01,730 --> 00:32:06,274
♫ let the cold remind you ♫

362
00:32:06,274 --> 00:32:08,384
I was jealous.

363
00:32:08,384 --> 00:32:10,027
Of what?

364
00:32:10,745 --> 00:32:13,088
You had somewhere else to go.

365
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:16,600
But I was stuck there.

366
00:32:23,808 --> 00:32:25,909
What do you want to be?

367
00:32:28,104 --> 00:32:31,198
I don't know yet. You?

368
00:32:42,402 --> 00:32:44,895
All I know is that the ocean isn't for me.

369
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:00,686
This little brat!

370
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:02,437
It's not even 10k won or 20k won.

371
00:33:02,438 --> 00:33:04,106
But you stole 100k won?

372
00:33:04,107 --> 00:33:06,358
- It wasn't me.
- Don't you lie to me!

373
00:33:06,358 --> 00:33:09,945
How did you get the money to buy a motorcycle then?!

374
00:33:09,946 --> 00:33:13,073
I knew I shouldn't have trusted you!

375
00:33:13,074 --> 00:33:14,616
How dare you stab me in the back?

376
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:16,118
What are you doing?!

377
00:33:16,119 --> 00:33:18,404
You're not even sure he did it!

378
00:33:18,404 --> 00:33:19,788
You two are in this together, aren't you?

379
00:33:19,789 --> 00:33:22,040
I took pity on you because you don't have parents

380
00:33:22,041 --> 00:33:24,376
and this is how you repay me?

381
00:33:24,377 --> 00:33:27,879
Get out of here! You're both fired!

382
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:29,297
We will.

383
00:33:29,298 --> 00:33:31,842
But give us this month's paycheck!

384
00:33:32,585 --> 00:33:34,027
Get lost!

385
00:33:34,027 --> 00:33:35,887
Hey, here's your money!

386
00:33:35,888 --> 00:33:37,724
Here!

387
00:33:37,724 --> 00:33:39,991
Take every last penny!

388
00:33:39,991 --> 00:33:42,453
And don't ever come back!

389
00:33:42,453 --> 00:33:44,896
Darn it.

390
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:56,925
Hey.

391
00:33:58,390 --> 00:34:01,530
You didn't steal the money, did you?

392
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:07,494
Well, I...

393
00:34:15,278 --> 00:34:16,762
Hey!

394
00:34:16,763 --> 00:34:18,939
Where are you going?

395
00:34:22,330 --> 00:34:26,138
I don't know what I'll become

396
00:34:27,774 --> 00:34:30,509
but I won't live this humiliating life.

397
00:34:30,509 --> 00:34:35,340
♫ You, too, stay right there ♫

398
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:43,270
♫ Our happiest memories shine the most ♫

399
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:46,830
♫ It's all I ever wanted ♫

400
00:34:46,830 --> 00:34:50,170
Joy to the world!

401
00:34:50,171 --> 00:34:52,380
- Is this money?
- Hey, what's this?

402
00:34:52,380 --> 00:34:54,242
It's money!

403
00:34:54,242 --> 00:34:56,593
Hey, that's mine!

404
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:57,844
- We got lucky!
- That's mine!

405
00:34:57,845 --> 00:35:00,555
This is mine! What's wrong with you?

406
00:35:00,556 --> 00:35:03,391
- I was picking them up for you.
- No, thanks!

407
00:35:03,392 --> 00:35:06,170
- I was helping you.
- This is mine. Go away.

408
00:35:06,170 --> 00:35:07,729
Let's go.

409
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:10,198
We're professors, we don't need this.

410
00:35:10,198 --> 00:35:12,442
Gosh.

411
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:17,650
♫ You should stay there ♫

412
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:22,990
♫ Wish you'd stay without me ♫

413
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:28,458
Ever since, Yi Kang's been having

414
00:35:28,459 --> 00:35:31,645
cursed Christmas holidays.

415
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:37,493
But I think I'll be like her from now on, too.

416
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:45,400
- Bidam Shelter.
-This is Haedong Police Substation.

417
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,294
We found a suspicious vehicle down the mountain.

418
00:35:47,294 --> 00:35:49,729
A wanted man is presumed to be on the mountain.

419
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:51,147
Excuse me?

420
00:35:51,148 --> 00:35:54,719
It's an area closest to the Bidam Shelter. Have you seen a suspicious man?

421
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:57,529
He's a drug squad detective, wanted for bribery.

422
00:35:57,529 --> 00:36:00,148
His name's Yim Cheol Gyeong.

423
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,150
[Yim Cheol Gyeong]

424
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:17,008
How and what...

425
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:19,968
Where do I need to fix this?

426
00:36:31,814 --> 00:36:33,457
Gosh.

427
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:39,263
Hey! Where are you going?

428
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:49,123
What on earth?

429
00:36:49,123 --> 00:36:51,374
I think I should look for the Yim Cheol Gyeong guy.

430
00:36:51,375 --> 00:36:53,293
Yim Cheo— Are you crazy?

431
00:36:53,294 --> 00:36:56,212
He's a wanted criminal. And a drug squad detective.

432
00:36:56,213 --> 00:36:59,032
- What if he has a gun?
- Exactly.

433
00:36:59,032 --> 00:37:02,052
I heard a strange sound earlier from the 11 o'clock direction.

434
00:37:02,053 --> 00:37:03,830
It sounded like a gunshot.

435
00:37:03,830 --> 00:37:07,390
- It must be near here.
- Then you really shouldn't.

436
00:37:07,391 --> 00:37:10,727
There's no electricity, no radio. What if something happens to you?

437
00:37:10,728 --> 00:37:13,063
So hurry up and fix the generator.

438
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:15,507
- I'll go look by myself.
- Hey!

439
00:37:15,507 --> 00:37:18,151
You said Yi Kang knows him.

440
00:37:18,151 --> 00:37:20,462
All the more reason to find him.

441
00:37:36,190 --> 00:37:38,547
Hello?

442
00:37:38,547 --> 00:37:40,474
Anyone?

443
00:37:42,034 --> 00:37:43,986
Over here!

444
00:37:54,063 --> 00:37:56,215
Are you all right?

445
00:37:56,215 --> 00:37:57,816
Are you from the shelter?

446
00:37:57,817 --> 00:38:00,819
Yes, from Bidam Shelter.

447
00:38:03,155 --> 00:38:04,823
Is this your first time hiking?

448
00:38:04,824 --> 00:38:06,950
You sprained your ankle because

449
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,961
you wore new shoes to the snowy mountain without breaking them in first.

450
00:38:11,272 --> 00:38:14,082
Plus, you have no crampons.
(Hiking shoes with sharp spikes)

451
00:38:20,214 --> 00:38:22,550
Senior Cheol Gyeong...

452
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:26,803
Has a man named Yim Cheol Gyeong come to the shelter?

453
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:29,323
He probably went to find a lost article.

454
00:38:29,323 --> 00:38:33,960
He's in his mid-thirties, about 180cm. Have you seen him?

455
00:38:35,579 --> 00:38:38,049
No. He didn't come.

456
00:38:38,049 --> 00:38:41,685
That's impossible. I'm sure he did.

457
00:38:42,503 --> 00:38:46,248
Take me to the shelter. Please.

458
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:49,293
I'm a detective in the drug squad.

459
00:38:49,293 --> 00:38:52,996
One of my seniors got wrongfully accused of getting bribes from a drug cartel.

460
00:38:52,997 --> 00:38:56,559
He said the evidence to prove his innocence is in the shelter.

461
00:38:56,559 --> 00:38:58,185
I have to go get that.

462
00:38:58,185 --> 00:39:01,129
Why is such an important object in the shelter?

463
00:39:01,130 --> 00:39:05,025
He said he has set up a spy in the cartel.

464
00:39:05,025 --> 00:39:08,303
They've been meeting up on Jirisan, away from prying eyes.

465
00:39:08,304 --> 00:39:12,066
And the informer once again left evidence at the shelter.

466
00:39:12,066 --> 00:39:14,559
Why am I doing this?

467
00:39:16,145 --> 00:39:18,989
I should've learned when Il Hae fixed it.

468
00:39:23,002 --> 00:39:24,753
What in the world?

469
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,341
We're from Gunsan Police Station, Cheongmun audit.

470
00:39:46,342 --> 00:39:49,844
Are you here for the wanted car? I think the wanted man went up the moun–

471
00:39:49,845 --> 00:39:51,930
- We're aware.
- The time is...

472
00:39:51,931 --> 00:39:53,473
- Sorry?
- What about Bidam Shelter?

473
00:39:53,474 --> 00:39:55,334
Can you reach them?

474
00:39:55,334 --> 00:39:58,895
I sent the search for the wanted man, but they are not answering their phone.

475
00:39:58,896 --> 00:40:01,856
I called the main station, but we can't radio them either as of now.

476
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:05,026
Call the National Park again. We must go up to the mountain now.

477
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:06,362
Okay. I got it.

478
00:40:21,585 --> 00:40:23,671
Why? Is it not working?

479
00:40:25,005 --> 00:40:27,216
- Let's go to the shelter.
- Thank you.

480
00:40:28,092 --> 00:40:29,843
It's not because of your coworker.

481
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:32,137
It takes more than two hours to go down the mountain

482
00:40:32,138 --> 00:40:33,888
but only an hour to the shelter.

483
00:40:33,889 --> 00:40:37,601
Stay the night there and go down tomorrow when it clears up.

484
00:40:40,104 --> 00:40:42,148
- Can you get up?
- Yes.

485
00:40:47,528 --> 00:40:50,738
What was the thing Cheol Gyeong was coming to get?

486
00:40:50,739 --> 00:40:52,783
A blue rucksack.

487
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:05,738
The sound came from 11 o'clock.

488
00:41:05,738 --> 00:41:10,376
If he started climbing from where the car was found, it must be near here.

489
00:41:31,689 --> 00:41:33,198
Excuse me, Sir!

490
00:41:33,199 --> 00:41:34,491
Wake up!

491
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,468
Don't fall asleep.

492
00:41:43,584 --> 00:41:45,793
Just a bit further.

493
00:41:45,794 --> 00:41:47,571
Hang in there.

494
00:41:59,516 --> 00:42:01,476
Where did he go instead of fixing the generator?

495
00:42:01,477 --> 00:42:04,187
What if it freezes with the door wide open?

496
00:42:15,282 --> 00:42:17,442
Wait here, please.

497
00:42:47,773 --> 00:42:50,475
Jung Goo Yeong! Jung Goo Yeong!

498
00:42:57,908 --> 00:42:59,543
Put that down.

499
00:43:02,204 --> 00:43:04,489
I said put it down.

500
00:43:21,140 --> 00:43:23,934
Hello, this is the police.

501
00:43:23,934 --> 00:43:27,045
Hello? Can you hear me?

502
00:43:32,620 --> 00:43:33,980
[Bidam Shelter]

503
00:43:43,695 --> 00:43:46,707
Why didn't you pick up your phone? What happened?

504
00:43:46,707 --> 00:43:49,625
We're on the mountain. There was no signal.

505
00:43:49,626 --> 00:43:52,571
The evidence? Did you find it?

506
00:43:52,571 --> 00:43:55,950
I looked everywhere, but I don't see it.

507
00:43:55,950 --> 00:43:58,217
Cheol Gyeong didn't say what it was either.

508
00:43:58,218 --> 00:44:00,412
She said it was a blue rucksack.

509
00:44:02,206 --> 00:44:03,973
Are you sure?

510
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:06,768
I searched before, but there was nothing special in it.

511
00:44:06,769 --> 00:44:09,255
She told me this was it.

512
00:44:09,255 --> 00:44:13,442
This rucksack is no different than the others. There's no proof that we've received bribes.

513
00:44:13,442 --> 00:44:16,269
She definitely said it was a blue rucksack!

514
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:20,724
This jerk, Yim Cheol Gyeong lied.

515
00:44:20,724 --> 00:44:23,494
There was no evidence, to begin with.

516
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:26,796
Why on earth?

517
00:44:50,700 --> 00:44:52,300
Stay still.

518
00:44:57,820 --> 00:44:59,713
Are you okay?

519
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:10,540
Freeze!

520
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:14,945
Detective Yim was right.

521
00:45:14,945 --> 00:45:17,840
The real criminal did show up.

522
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:20,808
But I didn't think there would be two.

523
00:45:23,637 --> 00:45:25,572
Senior, are you all right?

524
00:45:55,611 --> 00:45:58,572
"The Host" has set a new record

525
00:45:58,572 --> 00:46:01,340
just 38 days since its release.

526
00:46:01,341 --> 00:46:03,234
Grandma!

527
00:46:06,138 --> 00:46:08,031
What?

528
00:46:09,308 --> 00:46:10,350
No way!

529
00:46:10,350 --> 00:46:11,726
My turn!

530
00:46:11,727 --> 00:46:13,895
Take this.

531
00:46:13,896 --> 00:46:15,813
You're taking all!

532
00:46:15,814 --> 00:46:17,482
I thought you were dying sick.

533
00:46:17,483 --> 00:46:19,459
You're taking everything.

534
00:46:19,459 --> 00:46:21,227
Grandma!

535
00:46:22,362 --> 00:46:24,740
You said you were dying sick.

536
00:46:24,740 --> 00:46:27,681
You guys. Grab her!

537
00:46:30,370 --> 00:46:32,238
You!

538
00:46:34,130 --> 00:46:35,250
[National Park]

539
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:36,250
What's wrong with you?

540
00:46:36,251 --> 00:46:39,462
What are you doing, lying to your granddaughter?

541
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:41,255
Shut it! You'd run away

542
00:46:41,256 --> 00:46:44,967
and haven't visited your old grandma in years!

543
00:46:44,968 --> 00:46:47,637
- Whatever! I'm going back to Seoul!
- Oh, no!

544
00:46:47,638 --> 00:46:48,889
Leave me alone.

545
00:46:49,765 --> 00:46:51,808
Hey!

546
00:46:51,809 --> 00:46:52,934
You!

547
00:46:52,935 --> 00:46:55,495
What a temper. Hey!

548
00:46:57,356 --> 00:46:58,481
I said no.

549
00:46:58,482 --> 00:46:59,857
Why are you doing this?

550
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:02,836
Why?

551
00:47:02,836 --> 00:47:04,821
What will you do in Seoul?

552
00:47:04,822 --> 00:47:08,741
I've watched you until now, but what have you done there?

553
00:47:08,742 --> 00:47:12,995
Did you go to college or get a job?

554
00:47:12,996 --> 00:47:14,706
Gosh.

555
00:47:14,706 --> 00:47:17,667
You know, I hate mountains!

556
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:18,900
What?

557
00:47:18,961 --> 00:47:20,086
Just look.

558
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:22,523
They give bonus points to local residents.

559
00:47:22,523 --> 00:47:25,466
And no college degree is required.

560
00:47:25,467 --> 00:47:28,052
Just work here.

561
00:47:28,053 --> 00:47:30,596
Why are you doing this?

562
00:47:30,597 --> 00:47:32,307
You're killing me.

563
00:47:34,601 --> 00:47:36,727
You're all grown up now!

564
00:47:36,728 --> 00:47:39,564
You've always crawled up to the mountains.

565
00:47:39,565 --> 00:47:41,482
And now you're saying you hate them?

566
00:47:41,483 --> 00:47:43,618
Go! Go in!

567
00:47:48,574 --> 00:47:50,157
Over here!

568
00:47:50,158 --> 00:47:51,993
Hurry up and go in!

569
00:47:51,994 --> 00:47:54,370
Hey! Come here!

570
00:47:54,370 --> 00:47:56,360
[2006 National Park Special Appointment Interview]

571
00:48:15,517 --> 00:48:17,435
- Why did you apply?
- No reason.

572
00:48:17,436 --> 00:48:20,022
I don't want to work here. I hate the mountains.

573
00:48:20,480 --> 00:48:22,566
Tell me. Why did you apply?

574
00:48:25,944 --> 00:48:28,671
Are you still afraid of the mountains?

575
00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:34,785
Not bad.

576
00:48:34,786 --> 00:48:39,608
It's better than underestimating the mountains.

577
00:48:39,608 --> 00:48:42,853
There aren't many applicants around your age.

578
00:48:42,853 --> 00:48:46,389
- Give it a try.
- No, thanks.

579
00:48:51,178 --> 00:48:55,924
Do you still think that

580
00:48:55,924 --> 00:48:58,634
I made your parents die?

581
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:08,862
Then, why don't you save people from now on?

582
00:49:10,964 --> 00:49:13,499
I couldn't save them

583
00:49:13,951 --> 00:49:16,302
but you're different from me.

584
00:49:20,315 --> 00:49:23,994
If you're scared that people die up there,

585
00:49:23,994 --> 00:49:26,104
save their lives...

586
00:49:27,055 --> 00:49:29,499
before they die.

587
00:49:40,045 --> 00:49:45,215
Well, it seems like you don't have anything important to do from your resume.

588
00:49:51,196 --> 00:49:53,264
Show us what you've got here.

589
00:49:58,537 --> 00:49:59,955
Whatever!

590
00:50:05,719 --> 00:50:08,988
No drinking during hiking.

591
00:50:08,988 --> 00:50:12,074
I've been climbing Jirisan for 50 years.

592
00:50:12,074 --> 00:50:13,743
I can climb with my eyes closed.

593
00:50:13,743 --> 00:50:16,896
If you keep doing this, I'll tell your wife.

594
00:50:16,896 --> 00:50:20,450
I'll return this to you when you go down.

595
00:50:24,312 --> 00:50:26,772
You could've talked to him. Stop calling me over.

596
00:50:26,773 --> 00:50:29,551
People like him never listen to me.

597
00:50:29,551 --> 00:50:31,920
You're so good at this, though.

598
00:51:01,833 --> 00:51:04,160
I came to find a lost article.

599
00:51:35,010 --> 00:51:39,780
[Police notebook, thermos]

600
00:52:07,232 --> 00:52:09,142
Is this it?

601
00:52:13,113 --> 00:52:14,650
Thanks.

602
00:52:14,650 --> 00:52:18,880
[Bidam Shelter]

603
00:52:18,880 --> 00:52:21,520
You're managing the lost articles pretty tightly.

604
00:52:21,520 --> 00:52:24,740
Only the owner can take the lost items, right?

605
00:52:24,740 --> 00:52:27,930
Right, since you have to know what you're looking for.

606
00:52:40,974 --> 00:52:43,392
Are you a cop now?

607
00:52:43,392 --> 00:52:46,370
I'm just a low-rank constable for now.

608
00:52:46,370 --> 00:52:50,101
You said you didn't want to live a humiliating life, and you got what you wanted.

609
00:52:51,309 --> 00:52:53,219
You too.

610
00:52:57,015 --> 00:53:00,010
You look better with mountains than seas.

611
00:53:10,170 --> 00:53:11,988
By the way...

612
00:53:16,802 --> 00:53:19,340
I have something to tell you.

613
00:53:22,015 --> 00:53:23,783
What is it?

614
00:53:26,578 --> 00:53:28,287
Well...

615
00:53:29,689 --> 00:53:31,174
I...

616
00:53:37,472 --> 00:53:39,156
You know, before...

617
00:53:39,156 --> 00:53:42,270
An SOS report! Cardiac arrest!

618
00:53:46,260 --> 00:53:54,350
♫ The memories that I erased ♫

619
00:53:54,350 --> 00:53:59,170
♫ in white are colored with yellow ♫

620
00:53:59,170 --> 00:54:01,579
Will I see you if I come back here?

621
00:54:01,579 --> 00:54:03,656
I'll visit often.

622
00:54:03,656 --> 00:54:07,360
See you again.

623
00:54:07,400 --> 00:54:18,200
♫ ...it's drawn bigger with blue light ♫

624
00:54:18,270 --> 00:54:26,170
♫ Sometimes it turns red ♫

625
00:54:26,170 --> 00:54:33,190
♫ But even if you make me sad ♫

626
00:54:33,190 --> 00:54:38,350
♫ It came off white ♫

627
00:54:38,350 --> 00:54:46,200
♫ One more time, that memory ♫

628
00:54:46,200 --> 00:54:54,290
♫ It's colored yellow ♫

629
00:54:54,300 --> 00:55:06,200
♫ And we are like a dream in the same space ♫

630
00:55:06,250 --> 00:55:11,970
♫ I can draw it blue ♫

631
00:55:26,589 --> 00:55:28,232
Seriously...

632
00:55:29,992 --> 00:55:33,150
I thought he would die.

633
00:55:35,623 --> 00:55:37,575
Are you okay?

634
00:55:40,128 --> 00:55:41,779
Yes.

635
00:55:41,779 --> 00:55:45,030
Liar. You're obviously not.

636
00:55:48,203 --> 00:55:53,514
I can understand why you keep saying you want to quit.

637
00:55:54,142 --> 00:55:56,435
Let's both quit.

638
00:55:56,435 --> 00:55:59,104
I don't think I can do this.

639
00:55:59,104 --> 00:56:01,082
No.

640
00:56:02,342 --> 00:56:04,694
I won't quit.

641
00:56:07,922 --> 00:56:10,880
I'm going to stay here with this mountain.

642
00:56:36,083 --> 00:56:37,726
It'll hurt.

643
00:56:39,145 --> 00:56:40,463
Bear with it.

644
00:56:40,463 --> 00:56:44,733
Someone slammed me down and I don't remember anything after that.

645
00:56:44,734 --> 00:56:46,928
What happened?

646
00:56:47,996 --> 00:56:51,432
Rest for a bit. I'll bring you some water.

647
00:56:51,432 --> 00:56:54,140
So much blood.

648
00:56:56,079 --> 00:56:58,872
Is this all my blood?

649
00:57:09,509 --> 00:57:11,827
It's been a while.

650
00:57:11,827 --> 00:57:14,010
Yes, it has.

651
00:57:16,141 --> 00:57:19,944
I'm sorry. I didn't think it'd get this dangerous.

652
00:57:19,944 --> 00:57:25,820
On top of the weather condition, the plans got changed at the last minute.

653
00:57:31,489 --> 00:57:34,516
I didn't know you were still here.

654
00:57:34,516 --> 00:57:38,438
I haven't seen you once here, so I thought you quit.

655
00:57:38,438 --> 00:57:41,165
Did you come here often after that?

656
00:57:42,167 --> 00:57:43,693
Yes.

657
00:57:44,502 --> 00:57:47,410
You should've called me.

658
00:57:55,046 --> 00:58:00,150
Actually, I need to make a confession.

659
00:58:02,212 --> 00:58:03,696
What is it?

660
00:58:06,816 --> 00:58:09,126
You were right.

661
00:58:09,126 --> 00:58:12,037
The money...

662
00:58:12,037 --> 00:58:14,315
I stole that money.

663
00:58:18,503 --> 00:58:22,147
Really? Why?

664
00:58:22,147 --> 00:58:24,740
I wanted a motorcycle.

665
00:58:26,277 --> 00:58:29,150
To take you to the beach.

666
00:58:34,828 --> 00:58:36,830
A few months later,

667
00:58:36,830 --> 00:58:39,812
I returned the money and apologized to the owner.

668
00:58:39,812 --> 00:58:45,652
I was going to tell you the last time we met but I couldn't.

669
00:58:45,652 --> 00:58:48,607
I was too embarrassed.

670
00:58:49,943 --> 00:58:55,447
I wanted to tell you if we ran into each other here

671
00:58:55,447 --> 00:58:58,150
but I guess Jirisan is big and wide.

672
00:58:59,477 --> 00:59:01,470
It took this long.

673
00:59:06,860 --> 00:59:09,045
I'm sorry I lied.

674
00:59:12,140 --> 00:59:15,300
Aren't you embarrassed now?

675
00:59:15,300 --> 00:59:19,421
I'm fine. Maybe because I'm much older now.

676
00:59:20,707 --> 00:59:24,251
I'll call you next time when I come here for hiking.

677
00:59:25,770 --> 00:59:28,400
My wife loves the mountains, too.

678
00:59:44,289 --> 00:59:46,190
Bring proper shoes, clothes, and gear next time.

679
00:59:46,190 --> 00:59:49,210
Don't bug me by getting lost or something.

680
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:55,616
Okay.

681
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,550
Where are the pockets?

682
01:00:04,120 --> 01:00:06,090
So cold.

683
01:00:21,510 --> 01:00:24,480
[Jirisan National Park Haedong Ranger Station]

684
01:00:36,270 --> 01:00:39,117
We'll ask for your help as witnesses later.

685
01:00:39,117 --> 01:00:42,680
- Thank you for everything.
- Sure.

686
01:00:44,974 --> 01:00:46,851
I'll call you.

687
01:00:59,455 --> 01:01:01,732
Hey! Hey! Hey!

688
01:01:01,732 --> 01:01:04,910
So that's Yim Cheol Gyeong?

689
01:01:06,604 --> 01:01:08,673
Right?

690
01:01:08,673 --> 01:01:09,690
Right?

691
01:01:12,108 --> 01:01:13,970
Gosh, you.

692
01:01:13,970 --> 01:01:17,289
I'm hurt.

693
01:01:17,289 --> 01:01:18,783
Are you all right?

694
01:01:18,783 --> 01:01:20,534
Yang Sun! What are you doing here?

695
01:01:20,534 --> 01:01:23,620
Are you all right? I heard you got hurt.

696
01:01:23,620 --> 01:01:26,510
Well, I'm not badly hurt or anything.

697
01:01:28,351 --> 01:01:29,994
But...

698
01:01:32,255 --> 01:01:34,498
Maybe I'm wrong.

699
01:01:34,498 --> 01:01:37,993
- Are you here because of me?
- Yes, I was worried.

700
01:01:39,195 --> 01:01:41,264
You didn't even show up yesterday.

701
01:01:41,264 --> 01:01:43,940
What? What do you mean I didn't show up?

702
01:01:43,940 --> 01:01:45,880
I did.

703
01:01:45,884 --> 01:01:48,862
Were you there?

704
01:01:49,689 --> 01:01:54,930
You wanted to meet outside the theater, but you didn't come.

705
01:01:58,350 --> 01:02:02,570
[4:02, December 24th]

706
01:02:02,570 --> 01:02:06,230
[Jung Goo Yeong]

707
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:22,964
I was wondering what happened to you.

708
01:02:22,964 --> 01:02:25,782
I waited at the ticket box.

709
01:02:25,782 --> 01:02:28,110
You said outside the theater.

710
01:02:32,999 --> 01:02:37,569
Why didn't you call each other then?

711
01:02:37,569 --> 01:02:39,888
I didn't want to pressure her.

712
01:02:39,888 --> 01:02:43,650
I also figured something came up.

713
01:02:45,736 --> 01:02:47,246
So you did come.

714
01:02:47,246 --> 01:02:51,020
It was freezing yesterday. Are you okay? Didn't you catch a cold?

715
01:02:52,652 --> 01:02:55,937
I'm fine. What about your wound?

716
01:02:55,937 --> 01:02:58,790
It's only a scratch.

717
01:03:09,535 --> 01:03:11,745
Did you run?

718
01:03:11,745 --> 01:03:13,322
Yes.

719
01:03:17,927 --> 01:03:19,812
They're so frustrating.

720
01:03:20,780 --> 01:03:23,170
Let's leave them alone.

721
01:03:26,700 --> 01:03:33,400
♫ When there are people who think of me ♫

722
01:03:34,580 --> 01:03:40,700
♫ At that moment, my heart shrinks ♫

723
01:03:40,700 --> 01:03:48,000
♫ The truth within their clear eyes ♫

724
01:03:48,770 --> 01:03:56,070
♫ Makes me smile and makes me stand up ♫

725
01:03:56,070 --> 01:04:03,120
♫ I do not want to be without you ♫

726
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:10,260
♫ I don't want to let go of the hand that I hold ♫

727
01:04:12,110 --> 01:04:17,570
♫ I will always be by your side ♫

728
01:04:18,370 --> 01:04:26,260
♫ Although life squeezes me and torments me ♫

729
01:04:26,300 --> 01:04:33,400
♫ I am you like the blue light embroidered in the dark night sky ♫

730
01:04:33,470 --> 01:04:42,900
♫ I will always be by your side, like now, with you ♫

731
01:04:49,100 --> 01:04:56,800
♫ When did this happen to my heart ♫

732
01:04:56,810 --> 01:05:03,990
♫ The smile will never leave my lips again ♫

733
01:05:15,810 --> 01:05:19,122
How pathetic is this?

734
01:05:19,122 --> 01:05:23,352
Everyone else is enjoying Christmas. But what are we doing here?

735
01:05:23,352 --> 01:05:26,540
This is why I really hate Christmas.

736
01:05:30,301 --> 01:05:34,527
Did you really like Cheol Gyeong that much?

737
01:05:34,527 --> 01:05:38,032
So much that you couldn't leave the mountain?

738
01:05:38,032 --> 01:05:39,401
What on earth are you talking about?

739
01:05:39,401 --> 01:05:42,070
- I think it's true.
- It's not.

740
01:05:42,070 --> 01:05:43,839
Then what?

741
01:05:43,839 --> 01:05:46,274
Why do you keep saying you hate the mountains,

742
01:05:46,275 --> 01:05:49,600
but stuck around here for years as a ranger?

743
01:05:51,013 --> 01:05:53,866
I don't know why I'm doing this.

744
01:05:53,866 --> 01:05:55,200
Gosh, my life.

745
01:05:55,201 --> 01:05:58,400
That's sweet potato makgeolli.

746
01:06:02,370 --> 01:06:04,670
That's good.

747
01:06:17,640 --> 01:06:23,242
You want to know why I became a ranger?

748
01:06:29,702 --> 01:06:33,521
I was six...

749
01:06:35,266 --> 01:06:37,559
when I first climbed the mountain.

750
01:06:47,712 --> 01:06:49,864
This way.

751
01:06:49,864 --> 01:06:53,241
- All right.
- Put her down here.

752
01:06:53,241 --> 01:06:55,469
Oh, dear.

753
01:06:55,469 --> 01:06:58,538
- What's happening here? Gosh.
- Goodness.

754
01:06:58,538 --> 01:07:00,315
What will we do with her?

755
01:07:00,315 --> 01:07:04,810
So much hard work for you.

756
01:07:04,810 --> 01:07:06,670
I'm fine.

757
01:07:07,938 --> 01:07:09,774
That was so much work.

758
01:07:09,775 --> 01:07:11,243
Not at all. I should get going now.

759
01:07:11,243 --> 01:07:13,803
Oh, you came all the way here.

760
01:07:13,803 --> 01:07:15,664
Have some honey tea before you go.

761
01:07:15,664 --> 01:07:17,457
It's really all right.

762
01:07:17,457 --> 01:07:20,226
Of course, it's okay. This isn't the first time.

763
01:07:20,226 --> 01:07:24,464
It can't be easy carrying this darn-tall girl.

764
01:07:24,464 --> 01:07:27,192
I'll get you some tea. It'll be a second.

765
01:07:27,192 --> 01:07:28,719
Okay.

766
01:07:46,979 --> 01:07:50,924
I reached Cheonwangbong Peak for the first time at seven.

767
01:07:50,924 --> 01:07:54,152
By eight, I was able to go up alone.

768
01:07:54,153 --> 01:07:59,190
I brought a Coke and drank it there. It tasted like Heaven.

769
01:08:00,918 --> 01:08:04,312
And when I was nine, I started to walk along the ridges.

770
01:08:04,312 --> 01:08:07,682
You've never seen stars up there, right?

771
01:08:07,682 --> 01:08:10,143
It's awesome.

772
01:08:10,143 --> 01:08:13,220
She couldn't leave because she loves the mountains.

773
01:08:46,860 --> 01:08:50,190
♫ Every night I see you in my heart ♫

774
01:08:50,190 --> 01:08:53,480
♫ Every time I do I end up crying ♫

775
01:08:53,480 --> 01:08:58,570
♫ If I can you in the dark ♫

776
01:09:01,690 --> 01:09:06,940
♫ The place where the rising sun breathes ♫

777
01:09:06,940 --> 01:09:12,380
♫ I'm still stopping like this ♫

778
01:09:29,560 --> 01:09:32,670
[Jirisan]

779
01:09:32,670 --> 01:09:36,054
A wildfire has broken out on Jirisan.

780
01:09:36,054 --> 01:09:39,140
You said you saw a wildfire suppression banner?

781
01:09:39,140 --> 01:09:41,968
I need to find out where it happened.

782
01:09:41,969 --> 01:09:43,787
It can get to the village.

783
01:09:43,787 --> 01:09:47,273
If we find out where that is, we may know where the fire started.

784
01:09:47,273 --> 01:09:48,400
Where is that thing?

785
01:09:48,400 --> 01:09:50,193
Are you saying Yi Kang is still there?

786
01:09:50,193 --> 01:09:52,929
I don't know who that is, but he's trying to get me.

787
01:09:52,929 --> 01:09:54,364
Something happened?

788
01:09:54,364 --> 01:09:56,241
Senior, it's me.

789
01:09:56,241 --> 01:10:00,890
I know it's hard, but you should get mentally prepared.
